ntroduce latent defects across the SMF Γåö PCF Γåö CHF Γåö UDM interaction chain.	Confirmed E2E operational stability for the attdemo5g01 DNN, ensuring regression coverage integrity after CNRO provisioning changes. Successfully segregated core regression validation scope from unrelated observability dependencies (UDM summary traces), preventing unnecessary delays in regression certification activities. This disciplined scope management improved testing governance, dependency management, and validation clarity ΓÇö accelerating certification closure while preserving traceability for the outstanding observability item under a dedicated tracking ticket.	No additional regression actions required for this initiative. The remaining observability dependency related to UDM summary trace logging support is tracked separately under CTAP-75933 and will be validated independently. Ticket closed successfully with full regression certification achieved.	Led by: C├⌐sar Villagra | Tier 1 Involvement: No | Role: Technical Project Leadership ΓÇö end-to-end regression planning, execution oversight, scope governance, and dependency isolation management.	Supports IoT regression certification activities and confirms CNRO provisioning stability across the Darkstar / Northrim Labs environment. Demonstrates successful E2E validation governance and reinforces disciplined separation between core validation scope and observability dependencies. Contributes directly to overall platform stabilization readiness and release certification confidence for IoT-related DNN configurations.	All regression test cases passed successfully across SMF, PCF, CHF, CNRO provisioning, session establishment, and charging flows ΓÇö confirming that CNRO provisioning changes introduced no regressions in the attdemo5g01 DNN. The only non-blocking dependency identified was UDM summary trace logging support, which is an observability-layer item unrelated to the functional regression scope. This dependency was formally isolated and tracked under CTAP-75933 to preserve regression certification integrity. Classification: Successful regression validation with isolated observability dependency ΓÇö no functional defects detected.	C├⌐sar Villagra	f	configuration	{SMF,PCF,CHF,UDM,CNRO}		f	2026-05-27 21:03:21.174193+00	2026-05-27 21:03:21.174193+00	f	All regression test cases passed successfully with no functional defects identified. The only outstanding action item is related to UDM summary trace logging support, which is an observability dependency unrelated to the regression scope and is being tracked independently under CTAP-75933.
