emselves were succeeding at the CHF application layer, which masked the downstream observability failure. The combination of a configuration-layer deficiency (PCF Offline mode) and an observability-layer failure (Kafka CDR pipeline) created a scenario where usage was being processed but never reported ΓÇö a particularly insidious failure mode because it produces no immediate errors at the charging layer. After Tushar corrected the PCF configuration and the Kafka issue was resolved, full end-to-end visibility was restored. This pattern highlights the critical dependency between PCF session mode configuration and CHF Kafka pipeline health for accurate ACC reporting.	C├⌐sar Villagra	f	configuration	{CHF,PCF,Kafka,ACC}		t	2026-05-26 18:30:30.991942+00	2026-05-27 15:07:40.872877+00	f	\N
