50	1	3	02/09/2026-00050	CTAP-47429	2026-02-09	\N	PROVISIONING / SMSF	IoT Lab Environment	Closed	A SUPI provisioning deficiency was identified within the IoT Lab environment, disrupting DNN operational behavior and blocking downstream IoT service validation activities. Observed behavior: registration, connectivity, and service validation flows exhibited inconsistencies due to incomplete or incorrectly configured SUPI provisioning attributes ΓÇö specifically, missing P2P-related provisioning parameters required for proper DNN execution. Expected behavior: fully provisioned SUPI records with all required feature flags (including P2P) enabling seamless DNN behavior, registration success, and E2E IoT service validation. Technical context: the issue resided at the provisioning layer feeding into SMSF-related domains, with downstream impact propagating into DNN behavior, IoT service execution, and validation workflows. Affected flow: SUPI Provisioning ΓåÆ SMSF ΓåÆ DNN Behavior ΓåÆ IoT Registration / Connectivity / Service Validation (E2E).	Issue fully resolved and closed as of 02/18/2026. Coordinated investigation across provisioning, SMSF, and validation teams systematically narrowed the root cause from a broad set of potential domains (SMF, PCF, charging, transport) down to the provisioning layer specifically. Key finding: SMSF team review confirmed that critical P2P-related features were absent from the SUPI provisioning record. Once provisioning was corrected and a rebuild in Blackrim was executed, a final retest confirmed full restoration of expected DNN behavior. No residual provisioning inconsistencies were observed post-remediation. RCA confirmed: missing P2P feature enablement within SUPI provisioning data was the sole root cause.	Critical Testing Blocker ΓÇö Incomplete SUPI provisioning caused validation failures across IoT testing activities, incorrect DNN operational behavior, and delays in E2E validation execution. The issue created increased troubleshooting d