56	1	3	2026-03-19-00056	CTAP-59373	2026-03-19	\N	SMS / ACC / Visibility	ACC / Control Center / Ford IoT Validation Environment	Closed	A visibility disruption was identified in the ACC / Control Center reporting chain affecting SMS MT (Mobile Terminated) record ingestion for Ford IoT validation activities. Observed behavior: SMS MO (Mobile Originated) records were correctly reflected within Control Center, however SMS MT records were absent from the SMS records list following successful message execution. Expected behavior: Both MO and MT SMS records should be visible and reportable within the Control Center interface immediately after execution. Technical context: The issue resides within the ACC ingestion and Control Center synchronization layer ΓÇö not within SMS transport, IMS, or provisioning domains. SMS MT functionality was confirmed operational on other accounts, isolating the defect to a downstream reporting/visibility path specific to the Ford IoT validation environment. Affected flow: SMS MT Execution ΓåÆ ACC Ingestion ΓåÆ Control Center Reporting ΓåÆ Ford IoT SMS Validation Visibility.	The issue has been closed. Investigation confirmed that SMS MT execution was fully operational ΓÇö the defect was isolated to the ACC / Control Center downstream reporting and visibility layer. MO records were consistently reflected, while MT visibility remained inconsistent specifically within the Ford IoT validation context. SMS MT was verified as working correctly on other accounts, narrowing the scope to an account-specific or environment-specific ACC ingestion/synchronization behavior. The IoT and test team engaged Cisco for further clarification on the Control Center reporting inconsistency. RCA ruled out IMS, provisioning, transport, and network domains. The investigation was contained within ACC reporting, ingestion logic, and Control Center synchronization processes. The ticket was closed on 2026-03-25 following validation and coordination with the IoT team and Cis