alation governance, and project management oversight to ensure timely resolution aligned with Rivian OEM validation milestones.	Directly supports Rivian OEM charging validation and onboarding enablement by restoring end-to-end charging observability in the Darkstar environment. Demonstrates mature cross-domain RCA capability spanning PCF configuration, CHF processing, Kafka streaming, and ACC visibility layers. Highlights the critical dependency on CHF Kafka integration integrity for ACC visibility ΓÇö a systemic risk factor for all OEM charging validation activities. Improves organizational understanding of Online vs. Offline charging configuration impacts on observability pipelines. Contributes to charging observability stabilization and platform resiliency posture for release certification readiness.	Root cause was a dual-condition failure: (1) PCF charging configuration for the Rivian DNN was incorrectly set to Offline instead of Online on both rd2wa65 cpcf1 and rd2wa65 cpcf2 instances ΓÇö a configuration-layer defect identified and corrected by Tushar. (2) A CHF Kafka integration issue independently prevented CDR forwarding toward ACC, meaning even correctly generated charging records were not reaching the visibility layer. The SMF ΓåÆ CHF path (rdmwa65esme01 eSMF ΓåÆ 107.121.213.16) was validated as fully operational, confirming the issue existed exclusively downstream. Classification: Cross-domain charging visibility issue spanning configuration (PCF Online/Offline mode) and observability (CHF Kafka ΓåÆ ACC streaming) layers. The combination of these two independent failures created a complete ACC visibility blackout for Rivian charging, demonstrating how multi-layer defects can compound to produce symptoms that appear application-level but require infrastructure and configuration remediation.	Tier 1	t	configuration	{CHF,PCF,SMF,ACC,Kafka}		t	2026-05-27 18:55:39.243692+00	2026-05-27 19:03:31.721687+00	f	\N
