103	1	3	2026-04-07-00104	CTAP-66464	2026-04-07	\N	Charging / Working as Designed	Darkstar Labs ΓÇö Ericsson SMF/UPF, CHF, ACC, UDM, UDR, Charging Flows	Closed	Validation and root cause analysis of SID 60 CDR generation behavior within the Ericsson SMF charging environment in Darkstar Labs. The investigation was initiated after concerns were raised regarding the absence of SID 60 CDRs under specific testing scenarios, raising the question of whether the behavior represented a genuine charging defect or was aligned with expected platform design logic. The analysis encompassed the full E2E charging path including: TCP handshake behavior between UE and Ericsson SMF, charging trigger conditions governing conditional CDR generation, SMF ΓåÆ UDM ΓåÆ UDR query flows for DNN resolution, and SID 60 CDR lifecycle. During investigation, a secondary root cause was identified: the Ericsson SMF (eSMFe1-rdmwa65) issued a query to cUDM (cUDM-rdmwa75) for DNN 'attdemo5g01', but UDR responded with HTTP 404 Not Found due to the DNN being provisioned in UDR with uppercase characters, creating a case-sensitivity mismatch. Once the DNN resolution path was clarified, the SID 60 CDR generation behavior itself was confirmed as working as designed ΓÇö CDRs are generated only upon TCP handshake failure with the Ericsson SMF. Expected behavior: SID 60 CDRs should only be generated when the TCP handshake with Ericsson SMF fails; successful handshakes should not produce SID 60 CDRs. Affected flow: UE ΓåÆ Ericsson SMF ΓåÆ UDM ΓåÆ UDR (DNN resolution) ΓåÆ CHF ΓåÆ ACC (charging and CDR generation chain).	Investigation is complete and the ticket is closed as of 05/12/2026. The root cause analysis confirmed two key findings: (1) The SID 60 CDR generation behavior is functioning exactly as designed ΓÇö CDRs are produced only when the TCP handshake with the Ericsson SMF fails; successful handshakes correctly produce no SID 60 CDRs. (2) A secondary data provisioning issue was identified in the UDR layer: the Ericsson SMF (eSMFe1-rdmwa65) queried cUDM (cUDM-rdmwa75) for DNN 'attdemo5g01', and UDR returned a 404 Not Found error because the DNN had been provisioned with uppercase characters, causing a case-sensitivity mismatch. This provisioning discrepancy was the actual trigger for the observed anomaly in the charging flow. No application defect, charging defect, or policy routing issue was identified in the CHF, SMF, or charging application domains. The RCA was narrowed from a suspected charging defect to a confirmed working-as-designed behavior compounded by a UDR data provisioning case-sensitivity issue.	Charging Behavior Clarification | False Positive Defect Eliminated | Configuration Integrity Risk Identified. The investigation clarified that SID 60 CDR generation behavior is design-compliant, eliminating a false-positive defect classification that could have triggered unnecessary escalations toward Ericsson SMF, CHF, and charging application domains. Additionally, the identification of the UDR case-sensitivity provisioning mismatch (DNN uppercase vs. expected lowercase) exposed a data integrity risk in the UDM ΓåÆ UDR query resolution path that, if left unaddressed, could impact future DNN-dependent charging and session management flows across the platform.	Validated working-as-designed behavior in SID 60 CDR generation, preventing misclassification as a charging defect and avoiding unnecessary escalation toward Ericsson SMF, CHF, and charging application teams. Identified a secondary root cause in the UDR provisioning layer ΓÇö a case-sensitivity mismatch in DNN configuration ΓÇö that was producing 404 errors on the UDM ΓåÆ UDR query path. This dual-layer analysis accelerated troubleshooting by narrowing the investigation scope from a broad charging defect hypothesis to a confirmed design-compliant behavior combined with a discrete provisioning issue. The findings strengthened operational knowledge of conditional SID 60 generation logic, TCP handshake dependency, and DNN resolution sensitivity within Ericsson SMF environments, directly contributing to charging domain operational maturity and reducing future false-positive escalation risk.	No additional actions required. SID 60 CDR generation behavior confirmed as working as designed. UDR DNN provisioning case-sensitivity issue identified and documented. Ticket closed as of 05/12/2026. Recommended follow-up for future consideration: (1) Ensure DNN provisioning standards enforce consistent casing conventions in UDR to prevent recurrence of 404 resolution failures. (2) Document the TCP handshake failure trigger condition for SID 60 CDR generation in the Ericsson SMF operational runbook. (3) Share findings with Tier 1 and charging domain teams to prevent similar false-positive defect classifications.	Led by: Tier 1 | TPM Role: C├⌐sar Villagra ΓÇô Project Management Support. Tier 1 led the investigation and validation of the SID 60 CDR generation behavior and the UDR provisioning root cause analysis, with C├⌐sar Villagra providing project management coordination, escalation support, and executive documentation.	Charging Platform Integrity | Cross-Domain Stabilization | Operational Maturity Enablement. This initiative directly contributes to charging platform integrity by validating that SID 60 CDR conditional generation logic operates as designed within Ericsson SMF environments. The identification of the UDR case-sensitivity provisioning mismatch strengthens cross-domain stabilization by exposing a data integrity risk in the UDM ΓåÆ UDR resolution path. The combined findings improve troubleshooting efficiency, prevent false-positive escalations, and build institutional knowledge of Ericsson SMF charging trigger mechanisms ΓÇö contributing to overall charging domain operational maturity and readiness for future release certification cycles.	The SID 60 CDR generation behavior is confirmed as working as designed: CDRs are produced exclusively when the TCP handshake between the UE and Ericsson SMF fails; successful TCP handshakes correctly yield no SID 60 CDRs. The root cause of the observed anomaly was traced to a UDR data provisioning issue: the Ericsson SMF (eSMFe1-rdmwa65) queried cUDM (cUDM-rdmwa75) for DNN 'attdemo5g01', but UDR returned HTTP 404 Not Found because the DNN was provisioned with uppercase characters, creating a case-sensitivity mismatch in the resolution path. This means the issue spanned two layers ΓÇö the application layer (SID 60 CDR logic, confirmed design-compliant) and the configuration layer (UDR DNN provisioning, confirmed as the actual defect source). No charging defect, policy defect, or infrastructure defect was present. The failure path was: Ericsson SMF ΓåÆ UDM ΓåÆ UDR (404 due to DNN case mismatch) ΓåÆ no successful DNN resolution ΓåÆ downstream charging flow anomaly perceived as missing CDRs. Classification: working_as_designed (CDR logic) + configuration (UDR provisioning).	Tier 1	t	working_as_designed	{CHF,SMF,UPF,UDM,ACC}		t	2026-05-27 19:19:42.632882+00	2026-05-27 20:41:38.835745+00	f	\N
