isibility into Offer ID alignment processes, contributing to broader charging platform stabilization and release certification readiness.	Root cause is isolated to the CHF replication/synchronization layer ΓÇö not application-layer charging logic, PCF policy behavior, or Offer Management configuration. During Honda 5GSA testing, configured Offer IDs diverged from the active CHF database state due to a cross-environment replication failure (tracked as IOTQA-1154). The associated sub-issue CDEX-508236 was resolved independently and is no longer a contributing factor. The breakpoint is exclusively at the data synchronization layer between CHF environments: the CHF application logic itself processes correctly when given consistent data, confirming this is a replication defect rather than a charging logic defect. PCF logic, policy establishment, and application charging behavior have all been validated as functioning correctly, ruling out all upstream and downstream domains from the RCA.	Tier 1	t	replication	{CHF,ACC}		t	2026-05-27 19:19:10.129072+00	2026-05-27 20:41:40.648043+00	f	\N
